        "score": 0.6437693,
        "text": "The document is a section from the California Independent System Operator Corporation's Fifth Replacement Electronic Tariff, specifically Appendix BB, dated September 1, 2022. It outlines requirements for Asynchronous Generating Facilities:\n\n1. **Tripping and Performance**: Facilities may be tripped after a fault period if part of a Remedial Action Scheme. They must meet performance requirements through generating units or additional equipment.\n\n2. **Voltage Requirements**: The voltage at the Point of Interconnection must remain between 0.9 and 1.10 per-unit of nominal voltage for two seconds, excluding sub-cycle transients.\n\n3. **Exemptions**: Certain facilities may be exempt if they cannot comply with these requirements, provided they have a binding commitment with CAISO and a statement from the inverter manufacturer.\n\n4. **Frequency Disturbance Ride-Through**: Facilities must comply with off-nominal frequency requirements as per WECC guidelines.\n\n5. **Power Factor Design Criteria**: Facilities should operate within a power factor range of 0.95 leading to 0.95 lagging, with provisions for maintaining voltage schedules and dynamic voltage support.\n\n6. **SCADA Capability**: Facilities must provide SCADA capabilities for data transmission and reception to ensure system reliability.\n\n7. **Power System Stabilizers**: These are not required for Asynchronous Generating Facilities.",
